The President and First Lady will be hosting the White House Easter Egg Roll on April 13, 2020, on the South Lawn of the White House. Families with children aged 13 and younger are invited to join in the festivities. Tickets for the event can be requested through an online lottery from February 18 to February 24, 2020. Winners will be notified by email on March 4, 2020. The tickets are free and not for sale or resale. There are also volunteer opportunities available, and applications can be submitted from February 4 to February 11, 2020. Volunteers will be notified by email on February 21, 2020. Additionally, commemorative eggs will be available for the general public, with more information to be found on the lottery's website.